'''VR Chess''' is a cross-platform [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Game worlds|game world]] created by Nex1942. It was published in 2021. Many playable chess boards can be found within, allowing for multiple chess matches to be played simultaneously.

== Design ==
[[File:VR Chess Overview.jpg|thumb|Overview of VR Chess and some of its chess boards]]
The main attraction is the chess boards, which are scattered all across a modern house interior. There are two stories, the second of which has an internal balcony hanging over the main area.

== Chess boards ==
[[File:VR Chess Game in Session.jpg|thumb|A chess match is being played on one of the chess boards]]
Each chess board found in the world comes with extensive customization options.

=== Game modes ===
Besides Standard Chess, the modes [https://lichess.org/variant/atomic Atomic Chess], [https://lichess.org/variant/chess960 Chess 960], [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dark_chess Fog of War (aka. Dark Chess)] and [https://lichess.org/variant/crazyhouse Crazyhouse] may be chosen before starting the game.

=== Blitz Clock ===
The default clock is set at 10 minutes for each player. It can also be set to 15:00, 30:00, and 60:00 and an additional Increment of +2, +5, or +10 seconds can be set.
A game may also be played without any clock.

=== Visuals and sound ===
Each chess board has 3 different themes to pick from, which come in the form of a high-contrast default board, a marble board, and a wooden board.
The sound is on by default and may be turned off before starting a match.

=== Spectate ===
To better observe an ongoing match, anyone may enable a spectator mode, which opens up a large 2D view of the live board with all the pieces.

== Rating selection ==
While not found on each board itself, a player rating will show up on their play side, if set upon joining. This rating is set manually, but setting it truthfully helps to find matching opponents.
